<header>
	Look carefully at the bar chart and complete the sentences with a suitable comparative structure and any other words necessary.
</header>
	
<section id="body">
	<img class="rightFloat" src="../Media/AC_AW_005s.jpg" mode="1" id="1003"  /><img class="leftFloat" src="../Media/AC_AW_005.jpg" mode="16" id="1004"  /><br/><ol id="questionList"><li id="1">Twice <input id="q1" width="100" /> in Ukraine as in Estonia.</li><li id="2">The number of films produced in Romania was <input id="q2" width="100" /> as in Croatia.</li><li id="3">The number of films produced in Ukraine was <input id="q3" width="100" /> the number produced in Hungary.</li><li id="4">The number of films produced in Belarus was exactly <input id="q4" width="100" /> as the number produced in Slovenia.</li><li id="5">As <input id="q5" width="100" /> in Croatia as were produced in Estonia.</li><li id="6"><input id="q6" width="100" /> in the Czech Republic than in any other country in the chart.</li><li id="7"><input id="q7" width="100" /> in Belarus than in Hungary.</li><li id="8">The number of films produced in Slovakia was <input id="q8" width="100" /> the number produced in Slovenia.</li><li id="9">The number of films produced in Ukraine was <input id="q9" width="100" /> the number produced in Belarus.</li><li id="10">Four <input id="q10" width="100" /> in Hungary as in Estonia.</li></ol>
</section>
<section id="rt2001">
	<p align="left">In Unit 1 we saw how static charts do not show changes over time. If you are asked to write a report on a static chart, you will not have to describe trends, but you are expected to make comparisons between values.&nbsp;Here are some ways of making comparison.&nbsp;More films were produced in the Czech Republic than in Bulgaria.&nbsp;The number of films produced in the Czech Republic was double the number of films produced in Bulgaria.&nbsp;Twice as many films were produced in the Czech Republic as in Bulgaria.&nbsp;The number of films produced in the Czech Republic was twice as many as the number produced in Bulgaria. &nbsp;The number of films produced in the Czech Republic was twice as high as the number produced in Bulgaria.</p>
